Sprint 4 – System Enhancement and Future Improvements
Duration: Week 4
Sprint Goal
To enhance the system by improving performance, usability, and preparing for future scalability.
Tasks Completed
Reviewed overall system performance and identified limitations
Analysed inefficiencies in the Binary Search Tree (BST), particularly in worst-case scenarios
Refactored code to improve readability and maintainability
Improved menu system for clearer navigation and user experience
Added additional validation to handle incorrect user inputs
Explored implementation of advanced features (design stage only):
Filtering cars by multiple attributes (e.g., brand and price)
Sorting car listings
Researched self-balancing trees (e.g., AVL Tree) as a potential improvement
Sprint Outcome
System usability and structure were improved
Code quality enhanced for easier maintenance
Limitations of the current BST implementation were clearly identified
A roadmap for future improvements was established
Challenges Faced
Improving the system without changing the core structure
Balancing time between enhancements and documentation
Understanding more advanced data structures such as AVL Trees
Sprint Evaluation
Sprint 4 focused on refining the system rather than adding core functionality. This phase was important in identifying limitations and improving overall quality. It also demonstrated critical evaluation skills by analysing weaknesses and proposing realistic improvements.
